1.  The more you swing, the greater the chances of you hitting.  Which increases your chances of doing damage towards a mob.  <br>
More swings = More chances to hit = Greater potential to deliver damge<br>
<br>
2.  Evaluate the damage and delay of the weapon you are using.  I have a 23/40 2 hander and a Mith 2 hander 21/40 30% haste.  Now if i took the first weapon and placed on an FBSS i still dont perform as well as my Mith.  Even use Luthair's Damage Calc and it shows higher DPM for the Mith.  But this is just one example.<br>
<br>
3.  Balance yourself.  Do your best to have haste / ac / hp.  You can even consider resists and wis/mana, but more often than not you will have sets for these you switch to as need facilitates.  Having lots of haste but no hp or low ac items the higher level you are the more trouble you will be in because you will get hit more and cannot take damage as long as someone else.  Yes you may hit more during the short time you can stand there, but the longer you are attacking the mob also gives you more potential to do damage towards it was well.  Balance these factors.<br>
<br>
4.  For the original question Haste &gt; all then why dont some 50+ have it?  Any number of reasons.  Perhaps they are saving up to buy a nice uber haste instead of a lower haste item.  Maybe they are holding out to get a good haste drop and saving plat to upgrade other gear at the same time.  Maybe they arent guilded, play off peak hours and solo alot, and are poor and can't afford 3k for FBSS or dont even know how to do the Swift Claw Sash quest or tried 25 times and never got it and gave up.  Face it, some people take time to reasearch thier class, the game mechanics, and go for thie gear to optimize thier toon.  Other people don't do this for various reasons and just play the game.  I can think of plenty of reasons why they wouldnt have haste.  <br>
<br>
5.  Have fun.  <br>
<br>
