30% haste will make the mith far outperform 21% haste with the other weapon...<br>
<br>
I'm trying to educate the masses.<br>
I realize there's a million reasons or excuses or whatever for not having haste.<br>
And you can play however you want. But if you don't have haste. I am suggesting that you are doing significantly less damage than you should be, I am suggesting that you are being blinded by the visible ac numbers you see and are not taking into account correctly the unfortunately invisible number(haste) which in fact has the most significant effect on performance.<br>
<br>
You can use whatever you want in game. <br>
Verant really should put the haste values directly on the items. If they can show a number like the damage bonus on a weapon, why can't they show haste? It'd save alot of headaches and arguments and I bet if people actually had a number they could look at they'd use haste more.<br>
<br>
Angelsyn your arguments have nothing to do with anything really. You are just talking about maximizing your efficiency by taking into account which will be better. combinations of weapon and haste are irrelevant to the discussion anyway.<br>
We both agree that the hasted weapon is far better off than the unhasted one. You are just arguing about what ya can afford to maximize em.<br>
It's not like afterwards if you could afford a higher haste item you wouldn't get that as well to further increase your performance..... <br>
<br>
Regardless of what ratio weapon you are using, the final product from unhasted to unhasted is always the same  percentage better. My point is that the percent gained from being hasted is far superior to any absolute gain you get from ac. Gains in ac do not scale like haste does as ac is a straight number and haste is a percentage.<br>
<br>
Mobs dying faster is much preferred to mitigating more damage and the mobs dying slower. The end result is a huge savings in hp due to the mob not swinging when it's dead. heh. And that damage mitigated is far more than any ac boost can possibly give you. Period.<br>
<br>
This doesn't make any sense:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Yes you may hit more during the short time you can stand there, but the longer you are attacking the mob also gives you more potential to do damage towards it was well. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Last time I checked a mob had a set number of hit points. How can you do MORE damage to it? Once it's dead and you took 5k hp off it or whatever. If it took you 1 minute or 2 minutes you still only did 5k of damage.<br>
I guess the less damage you are doing and longer you are fighting the more it will regen so you have more hp to shave off it to kill it. lol. <br>
<br>
<br>
Anyway, if you are 50+ and making excuses or don't want to use a haste item that's fine. But don't expect to perform as well as you should. And when you can't solo places others can with ease, you'll know why.<br>
<br>
Biz.<br>
