If i had high haste, but low ac / hp, while im attacking mob, it is also attacking me.  If I cant take the damage long enough to kill the mob, the mob wins I lose.  I never stated you do more damage than the mobs hp I clearly meant that you should balance your toon.  Even if you are hasted very well, the longer you can take damage from the mob means the more damage you do to it.  Example: say your hasted DPM is 400 and all your damage goes thru.  The mobs hp is 1200.  You are standing toe to toe, no procs, nukes, dots just by pure DPM it would take you 3 min to kill the mob.  Say your hp is 800 and the mob does 300 dpm and all its damage go thru, you most likey would be dead by before the mob.  This is just an extremely basic situation, but if you were to get extremely technical you could prove the same thing, you must do as much damage as you can to the mob before the mob kills you.  The more hp you have , the longer you can stand there attacking the mob.  The more ac you have, the more you can avoid damage.  The more haste you have, the more you swing, the more chances you get to do more damage towards the mob.    <br>
1) Yes get haste<br>
2) Have a decent weapon to use with your haste.<br>
3) make sure you have decent AC<br>
4) make sure you have decent HP<br>
5)Dependant upon your situation, make sure u have the correct resists at a decent amount.<br>
6) And finally, <br>
I hope this is a little clearer now.  I never meant to imply anything else.   <br>
